s technische und gestalterische Planungsgrundlagen. Er bietet gezielt Informationen zu ausgeführten Beispielen bis in die konstruktiven Details. Die Charakteristika der Baustoffe werden dabei in ihrem besonderen Anwendungspotenzial und ihren spezifischen Bedingungen sichtbar. Eine umfassende Auswahl internationaler Anwendungsbeispiele zeigt verschiedene Lösungsansätze im Detail.  aIn recent years, facades have become more important in architectural practice and in public perception. As well as functioning as a protective shell and visible 'face' and supplying heat and electricity, a building's exterior interacts directly with the surrounding public space.This revised and expanded new edition of the Facade Construction Manual offers readers technical and design planning fundamentals in a compact reference work.A section describing a comprehensive selection of built structures shows general and unique, tried and tested, and innovative approaches to facade planning – down to the last detail.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFacades.1 aKrippner, Roland, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLang, Werner, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDETAIL eBook Package English 2001-2018z978311066216008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDETAIL eBook Package English 2001-2021z978311068956308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2018z9783110602999oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2018 Englishz978311060397208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTit